# 🚢 Titanic Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

## 📌 Project Overview

This project is a part of the **Data Science with Python Internship – Task 3** at **MainCrafts Technology**.

The objective of this project is to perform **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** on the Titanic dataset by cleaning the data, handling missing values, creating new features, and visualizing key insights using Python.

---

## 📂 Dataset

- Dataset: Titanic Dataset
- Source: Kaggle

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

---

## 📊 Project Tasks

### ✅ Data Cleaning
- Filled missing Age values using Mean
- Removed irrelevant column (Cabin)
- Created Age Groups
- Created Family Size feature

### ✅ Exploratory Data Analysis
- Survival Rate by Age Group
- Survival Rate by Embarkation Port
- Survival Rate by Family Size

### ✅ Visualizations
- Age Distribution Histogram
- Correlation Heatmap
- Survival Rate by Family Size
- Survival Rate by Age Group

---

## 📈 Key Insights

- Children had a higher survival rate than adults.
- Smaller families showed better survival chances.
- Passenger class and fare were strongly related to survival.
- Missing values were handled before analysis.

